@NODE boolean "Boolean Gadgets"

Boolean gadgets are the most common pre-kick 2.0 gadgets.  They're handled
by  intuition.library,  not  by  GadTools.library, so they haven't got any
tags  and  you can't use the GT_SetGadgetAttrsA() function with them.  You
could want to use them if you want a button gadget with some features that
the gadtools Button Kind doesn't have, e.g. @{"images" link "imgbank"}, toggle-select mode...

NOTE WELL:  in your sources, make sure you don't use the xxxGadget symbols
            as a  pointer  to  a  boolean  gadget,  beacuse  it  represent
            the Gadget structure!

Example: this piece of code would be wrong:

     [...]
     move.l  BooleanGadget,a0
     jsr     _LVOOnGadget(a6)
     [...]

You should write:

     [...]
     lea     BooleanGadget,a0
     jsr     _LVOOnGadget(a6)
     [...]

or in C:

     OnGadget( &BooleanGadget, .... );

Moreover,   there   aren't  pointers  to  gadgets  of  this  kind  in  the
<wnd>Gadgets array.


These are the gadgets you'll find in the Boolean Gadgets requester:

    - Label             the gadget label

    - Text              the text of the gadget. It will be used only if
                        the checkbox is checked.

    - X, Y              the coordinates of the text,  relative  to  the
                        upper-left corner of the gadget.

    - INVERSVID         if checked,  the text will be printed inversed.

    - Draw Mode         JAM1        the text will be printed  with  the
                                    Front  Pen  selected,  leaving  the
                                    background untouched.

                        JAM2        the text will be printed with  both
                                    the Front and Back pens selected.

                        COMPLEMENT  the  text   will   be   printed  in
                                    comlpementary mode.

    - Front Pen         the color of the text

    - Back Pen          the color of the background  (used only if draw
                        mode is JAM2).

    - W, H              the size of the gadget.

    - *                 copy the size of the image selected to the size
                        of the gadget.

    - Gadget Render     the @{"image" link "imgbank"} used to render the gadget. The symbol
                        (---) means NO IMAGE.

    - Select Render     the  @{"image" link "imgbank"}  used  to  render  the  gadget  when
                        selected.

    - Highlight         GADGHNONE       selecting the gadget  it  won't
                                        change.

                        GADGHCOMP       the   gadget    box   will   be
                                        complemented when the gadget is
                                        selected.

                        GADGHBOX        when the gadget is selected, it
                                        will have a box  drawn  around.

                        GADGHIMAGE      when   selected,   it  will  be
                                        renderd with the Select  Render
                                        @{"image" link "imgbank"}.

    - TOGGLESELECT      set the toggle-select mode for the gadget.

    - RELVERIFY         if set, you'll receive an IDCMP_GADGETUP message
                        when the gadget is released.

    - IMMEDIATE         if set, you'll be informed when the  gadget  is
                        activated.

    - FOLLOWMOUSE       set this bit  if  you  want  to  receive  mouse
                        movement reports while your gadget is active.
                        If you set this flags, you should also set  the
                        IMMEDIATE one. Moreover, if you want to receive
                        ANY mouse movement event you  should  set  also
                        the RELVERIFY flag.

    - DISABLED          the gadget will be created disabled.

    - SELECTED          the gadget will be created selected.
@ENDNODE

